com.nokia.places

Interface Category


  • public interface Category
    This interface represents a category with which a Place can be associated.

    Categories can be used to search for places based on the categories with which they are associated.


    See Also:
    Nokia's Restful Places API - The Category Media Type

      • getId

      • getIcon

        javax.microedition.lcdui.Image getIcon()
        This method retrieves the Icon associated with this category. NOTE: this is an optional attribute, can return null.
        Returns:
        An image containing an icon representing the category.

      • getWithinCategory

        java.lang.String[] getWithinCategory()
        This method retrieves the id(s) of the Category or Categories associated with the current category.

        The basic Categories are:

        • ACCOMMODATION
        • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREAS_BUILDINGS
        • EAT_DRINK
        • GOING_OUT
        • LEISURE_OUTDOOR
        • NATURAL_GEOGRAPHICAL
        • SHOPPING
        • SIGHTS_MUSEUMS
        • TRANSPORT
        All other categories lie within at least one basic category as well.

        Returns:
        An array containing the id (or ids) the Category lies within.

      • isWithin

        boolean isWithin(Category category)
        This method retrieves a boolean value indicating whether the Category lies within the specified Category or not
        Parameters:
        category -
        Returns:
        true if this Category is within the specified Category false otherwise.
